The U.S. Attorney's Office says Mystic Pizza's 48-year-old owner John Zelepos faces up to 15 years in prison . 
 He has pleaded guilty to tax evasion and financial structuring offenses . 
 Prosecutors between 2006 and 2010, Zelepos diverted just over $567,000 from Mystic Pizza's gross receipts . 
 He diverted the money into his personal bank accounts and those of family members, they said . 
 Prosecutors said Zelepos also made bank deposits under $10,000 to skip currency transaction reports filed by banks . 
